Thanks to rcasta.  Not bad, I was pleasantly surprised with this one.  It has champagne like characteristics, very bubbly and spicy.
Drank it with ghawener.  An ok IPA, too sweet for my taste buds.  However, very enjoyable indeed.
Drank it at the brewery, on a cold, sunny, crisp March day!!  I went to see the monks, they wont let you in, but they are very friendly.  Ill be back for sure.

Drank it at the brewery!!  Wow what a nice drive from Brugge.  I totally recommend it you make the effort and drive out there.  You do need a GPS it is in the middle of no where.  About the beer, enough has been said.  However, it is totally better at the brewery!  I am so lucky.
Thanks to ghawener who brought it all the way down from San Diego, California!!  Potent, you can really the 9.5% abv.  Solid, not very complex, but good.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada 30th Anniversary Fritz & Kens Ale

review_blob: Thanks to ghawener who brought it from San Diego California!!  A sweet porter with coconut undertones.  However, if you let it warm up, the coconut really comes out.  Wow!
Thanks to Ricardo Pavez who brought it all the way from the brewery in Valdivida, Chile!!!   Nice solid bock, easy to drink, some smoke and good malty flavor.
Thanks to rcasta, drank it in Coatepque Lake!!!  Really nice, well balanced, nice sweet and spicy.
Drank it at home with my wife paired with delicious sea salt, chile dark chocolate.  Pours dark brown with a light head.  Light bodied, silky, well balanced with hops, chocolate taste.

Drank it in a small, but very good restaurant in Antigua Guatemala.  I would say one of the best beers brewed between Mexico and Colombia.  Dispite its dark appearance, it is light bodied, balanced with a slight sweetness from the Malt-

Drank it with my wife in a beautiful hotel in Antigua Guatemala.  We paired it with a delicious sea salt and chili dark chocolate produced in Antigua.  Smooth, light bodied, silky, chocolate, some bitterness not much, might miss the hops, but a great alternative.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Chocolate Oak Aged

review_blob: Bottle.  Bought at Sunset Corner in Miami.  An above the average IPA, light bodied, can not taste the juniper, however it is spicey.
Drank it with ghawener for dessert paired with Zebra ice cream.  Delicious, silky and smooth mouthfeel, creamy, nice malt backbone, flavors of chocolate and coffee.
Drank it with ghawener.  Different from US IPAs, a stronger malt backbone very well balanced with the bitternes of the hop.  Very dry and long bitter finish.
Drank it with my father.  Very similar to a porter.  Pours pitch black with a nice tan head.  Sweet Aroma.  Medium bodied, roasted flavors, chocolate, dark chocolate.  Nice.
Drank it with my wife, while eating a delicious Vosges Red Fire Chocolate Bar.  Pours pitch black, medium bodied, nice roasted mouth feel, not sweet, rather dry with chocolate undertones.
Drank it with rcasta, rsamayoa and dageek in La Pepeshka.  Great Unibroue brew.  Medium bodied, nice citrus mouthfeel.
Drank it with rcasta, rsamayoa and dageek in La Pepeshka while traveling in the Bocana, Costa del Sol.  Delicious, light bodied, great for the beach, nice and sour.
Drank it with rcasta, rsamayoa and dageek in the Pepeshka while traveling in la bocana.  Medium bodied, creamy texture and mouthfeel.  Nice and balanced a tad sweet like toffee.
Drank it with the Castas during the Mexico - El Salvador.  Heavy bodied, thick mouth feel, great taste of dark chocolate, heavy on the alcohol nice warm feeling.  Too bad we lost!!
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: Bitter Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Drank it with the Castas during the Mexico-El Salvador game.  Heavy bodied, thick mouth feel, great taste of dark chocolate, some rum like characteristics.

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Thanks to rsamayoa, drank it at his birthday.  What a blast.  Full bodied like engine oil, exremely sweet, and over powering.  Alcohol very present.
Thanks to ghawener.  A pleasently, potent brew.   A lot of bourbon like characteristics, sweet, fruity and woody.  However, unlike bourbon, in this beverage we can truly enjoy the magic of hops!!

Thanks to ghawener.  Great appearance and aroma.  Light bodied for a stout, great initial mouth feel with distinct chocolate flavors.  However, ending is flat only the bittirness of the hops is present.

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: Drank it with ghawener for my god daughters b-day.  Wow.   Complex.  Multi layered flavors.  Heavy bodied, almost syrupy.  Changes with changes of temperature.  Best enjoyable at warmer temperatures, chocolate, rum, fruits, molasses, etc, etc, etc.

Drank it with rcasta and ghawener.  I thought I had tried it before, but guess not...Wow, this is what I love in a beer.  Medium bodied, full flavored, nice mouthfeel throughout.Earlier Rating: 8/8/2008 Total Score: 3.7Thanks to Juancho.  Drank it in Panajachel, Guatemala.  Pours nice golden, hazy color with a good white head.  Aromas of pine and grass.  Medium bodied, well balanced between malts and hops, nice complexity in the hop flavor, different levels of flavors along your mouth.
Drank it with ghawener and rcasta.  Good. Refresing, light bodied, citrusy.
Drank it with rcasta and ghawener.  Nice and balanced. Light bodied, slightly hoppy and no too sweet.
Drank it with rcasta and ghawener.  The best brown ale Ive tasted so far.  Slight hoppiness, nice, well rounded.  Light bodied but full flavored.
Drank it with ghawener.  Bottle Conditioned.  Medium bodied, unidimensional, not a lot of layers like other IIPAS.  Malty and alcohol is very present.
beer_name: Iron Springs Casey Jones Imperial IPA

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Thanks to pollo.  Drank it at Coatepeque lake with pollo and rcasta.  A really nice beer, light bodied yet complex flavored.  Not overly bitter and salty.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Thanks to pollo.  Drank it at Coatepeque Lake with pollo and rcasta.  Potent.  Heavy bodied, mouthfeel of christmas flavors, spices, cinammon, and candy.  Heart warming, and fulfilling.
beer_name: Lost Abbey Gift of the Magi

review_blob: Drank it while deep sea fishing in La Pepeshka with rcasta.  Pours a deep golden with tan head.  Medium bodied, nice balance of malts and hopiness flavors of pine and citrus.
Drank it with my wife and brother last nite, combined with Oaxaca dark chocolate.  Up my alley, nice notes of chocolate and smoke, perfectly balances with some smokiness.
On tap at San Franciscos City Beer.  By the way, great place I will rate it.  Pours dark amber, medium to full bodied, not too sweet, presence of hops which give it a dry ending.

Drank it at San Shi Go in Laguna Beach, CA.  My first sake rating.  Pours white and very cloudy, you have to shake every time you drink.  Smooth and silky, nice sweetness which hides very well the ABV of 15%.
beer_name: Sho Chiku Bai (Pine Bamboo Plum) Nigori Sake

review_blob: Drank it at San Shi Go in Laguna Beach.  Same as Yebisu.  Light, tasteless a bit skunky.  My friend Carla like it.
Drank it at San Shi Go in Laguna Beach.  Typical Pale Ale, no taste, watery, but drinkable.
Drank it at Brussels Bistro in Laguna Beach, CA.  This is a classic I hadnt had since high school.  Reminds me of Ultima Alucinacion.  Great Ale.
Drank it in Brussels Bistro in Laguna Beach, CA.  Medium bodied because of alcohol content, nice sweetness, some spices.
Drank it on tap at San Franciscos Toronado thanks to a friend we met from Nicaragua.  Pitch black color, seems heavy, however it is light bodied, smooth and creamy, roasted flavor.
Drank it on tap at San Franciscos Toronado.  Wow.  Really good IPA.  Nice complexity and level of flavors, starts citrus sweet and has a nice dry hoppy ending.
Drank it in Sacramento.  Tap.  Pours yellow cloudy with a thin white head.  Light bodied, smooth, subtle sweetness, refreshing.
Drank it at the Roxy in Sacramento.  Pours dark amber with tan head.  Medium bodied, smooth, fruity sweet, nice hoppy finish.
Drank it in Laguna Beach at Carlas house.  Medium to heavy bodied.  Malty sweetness mouthfeel, well complemented with the bitterness of the hops.
Drank it in San Franciscos Alioto with my family.  Cloudy appearance, light bodied, refreshing, good sweetness.
Drank it on tap at San Franciscos Toronado with my wife.  Always impressed by Sierra Nevada, great IPA, medium bodied, nice layering of hop flavors.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Fresh Hop IPA - Southern Hemisphere
